paragraph.materialsCitation:
Holotype , by monotypy: [Gulf of Aden], Djibouti , Baie de Tadjourah , [
6 February 1904
], one specimen 35/ 25 mm preserved, [leg. mission Charles Gravier] ( MNHN , no catalogue number). Vayssière dissected the type. Other malacologists may have reexamined it too. The radula is missing and probably lost. No slide was found at the MNHN. The reproductive system is present but in poor condition. In particular, it had been separated from the body wall and its distal part (with the accessory glands) was damaged.
